The Field Crickets are widely distributed worldwide, being more diverse in the Old World, in comparison to the New World, where the subfamily Gryllinae are less represented, although in recent years important contributions have been published, showing in America the taxaonmy is not yet settled (Jaiswara & Desutter, 2017; Cadena-Castañeda & García García, 2020 ). All the Field Crickets of the new world are included in the tribe Gryllini and divided into three sub-tribes: Anurogryllina , Brachytrupina and Gryllina with 20 genera ( Gorochov, 2019 ; Cadena-Castañeda & García García, 2020 ;
Cigliano et al ., 2021
).

Measurements are given in millimeters. Measures for conventional structures are presented like this: Specimens were measured with Vernier calipers. Parameters are as follows: 
Total length
(Tl), the distance between the frons and the apex of the abdomen; 
length of pronotal disc
(P), the distance from the anterior to posterior margin; 
length of tegmina
(Teg), the distance from the humeral sinus to the apex; 
length of hind femur
(Hf), from the base to base of genicular lobe; 
length of hind tibia
(Ht), from the base to the apex; 
length of ovipositor
(Ov): from subgenital plate to the apex.

